                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1250: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-30T22:00:00-04:32"
                            >June 30, 1931—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Department’s telegram No. 27.<note n="75" xml:id="d583fn75">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> I have just seen the Minister for Foreign Affairs who was receptive to
                    the idea of conversations with the neutral representatives here but stated that
                    he would have to see the President tomorrow morning at 9 o’clock to give a
                    definite answer which he will communicate to me at once. He stated that the
                    second Bolivian note had been delivered yesterday noon and that Guachalla would
                    not leave until 7 o’clock Thursday morning so there is still time for action. He
                    urged that Paraguay be sounded out on the same lines and be persuaded to accept
                    efforts of neutrals as it will place Bolivia in a difficult position if it does
                    not receive them favorably.</p>
                <p>I urge that I and the other neutral representatives here be given definite
                    instructions to go ahead so as to make it a collective and effective action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
